File: e2e/discovery-edge-cases.e2e.ts
- Every test: configDir/tmpDir created, startMcpServer called outside try. If startMcpServer throws, temp dirs leak.
- Affected test starts at approximately lines 54, 93, 140, 190, 243, 315.

Fix for both files: Move startMcpServer inside the try block, declare server as a let variable (possibly null), and add null check in finally:
```
let server: McpServer | null = null;
try {
  server = await startMcpServer(configDir, true);
  // ... rest of test ...
} finally {
  if (server) await server.kill();
  cleanupTestConfigDir(configDir);
  fs.rmSync(tmpDir, { recursive: true, force: true });
}
```

Import the McpServer type from fixtures.js where needed.

