File: e2e/analyze-site.e2e.ts

Issue 1 (line ~111): afterAll calls analyzeSiteServer.kill() without null check:
```
let analyzeSiteServer: TestServer;  // line 105
test.beforeAll(async () => {
  analyzeSiteServer = await startAnalyzeSiteServer();  // line 108
});
test.afterAll(async () => {
  await analyzeSiteServer.kill();  // line 112 — TypeError if beforeAll threw
});
```
Fix: Add a null check: `if (analyzeSiteServer) await analyzeSiteServer.kill();`
Also change the declaration to: `let analyzeSiteServer: TestServer | undefined;`

Issue 2 (lines ~256-258, ~301-303): Conditional assertions silently skip verification:
```
if (gqlEndpoint?.requestBodySample) {
  expect(gqlEndpoint.requestBodySample).toContain('query');
}
```
If requestBodySample is undefined (timing issue, regression), the test silently passes. Fix by making the assertion unconditional:
```
expect(gqlEndpoint?.requestBodySample).toBeDefined();
expect(gqlEndpoint!.requestBodySample).toContain('query');
```
Note: The exact line numbers may vary — search for `requestBodySample` to find both occurrences.
